NOTES:
1. Government consumption expenditures are services (such as education and 
   national defense) produced by government thatare valued at their cost of 
   production.  Excludes government sales to other sectors and government 
   own-account investment(construction and software).
2. Gross government investment consists of general government and government 
   enterprise expenditures for fixed assets; inventoryinvestment is included 
   in government consumption expenditures.



